You didn&#39;t initialize the member variables in setUp().  Instead you created
two local variables and initialized them (but these can&#39;t be seen outside of
setUp()).  The member variables are both initialized to null, by default, so
when you do a.plus(b) you are attempting to invoke the plus() method on a
null.

